text: You will fall in love with this FULLY RENOVATED Immaculate 2BR/2BA Apartment located on Main Street in downtown Ossining! This fully accessible ground-level unit is teeming with elegance and historic charm, offering many great amenities, including Central Air, BIG Closets, Hi-End Finishes, and an exposed brick wall. Just 48 minutes by Train to GCS (and just a few short blocks away), and Close to restaurants, recreation, and shopping! The apartment is on the first floor and has lovely light quality (including a few skylights!). Enjoy Hardwood Floors in bedrooms, Imported Stone Tile Floors in living/kitchen, and entry hall, Marble Countertops in Kitchen and Bathroom Vanity, plus Custom Wood Cabinets with Under Cabinet and lighting! All of the appliances are new and High Efficiency, including a Gas Range, Dishwasher, Washer & Dryer (inside the unit), Large refrigerator, and over-range microwave with Hood Built-in. The apartment also has a Large Pantry Closet with built-in Shelves, and the Closets in the Bedroom have built-in storage as well! Stow away suitcases and seasonal clothes in the Overhead Storage units in Bedrooms. Safety features include a Doorbell Buzzer System and Secured hallways with code locks at two locations. The unit also has high-speed Internet access, Wired for Optimum, and Verizon. You'll enjoy a bustling downtown area with proximity to the Metro North Train Station, as well as Markets, Restaurants, Cafes, a Pharmacy, a Bookstore, and a Post Office. Parking is Municipal by the Village of Ossining (you will need to get a tag for your car - not expensive!), with Multiple lots within 1 block. Ossining is an Artsy and Upcoming Community located along the majestic Hudson River with beautiful views! The unit can be accessed with zero steps and is wheelchair accessible. Tenant is responsible for utilities. Apply via RentSpree!

text: Welcome to a home entertaining experience like no other in the heart of Westhampton Beach Village, less than a half a mile from Main Street and a stone's throw to the village beaches, marina, and more! Where water views meet modern luxury, this home offers 4500 SF of custom exquisite craftsmanship by Coastal Management. Offering six bedrooms, six and two half bathrooms, open living spaces flooded with natural light, water views, wide white oak flooring throughout, floor to ceiling windows and doors, designer details & finishes and a plethora of space for family & friends. The upper level boasts the primary bedroom suite with private sunset viewing deck and hidden outdoor shower, there are two additional ensuite bedrooms and a media room. This level hosts the custom crafted Chef's Kitchen, with seamless cabinetry, top-of-the-line appliances, wet bar & wine refrigerator and oversized island with granite countertops. The open living and dining room offer access to another viewing deck with views to Dune Road and beyond. On the lower level there is an additional ensuite guest bedroom, plus a separate guest wing featuring a full kitchen, living room & den. With ample room and access to the outdoors, bonus features include, outdoor shower, fireplace and a garage. The exterior grounds, architecturally landscaped and designed, include a heated gunite saltwater pool & spa, covered porch & patio, BBQ and large private driveway. The opportunity to enjoy this unique & flawless work of art will not last long, now available August 2026!

text: Welcome to this exquisitely renovated four-bedroom, two-bath unit in a Nyack duplex where timeless charm meets modern sophistication. Enjoy seasonal Hudson River views from this fully reimagined home, offering two levels of thoughtfully designed living space. The main level features a chefs kitchen with quartz countertops, an oversized island, custom cabinetry, and premium stainless-steel appliances. The living room, with its gleaming hardwood floors, elegant wainscoting, and large panoramic window, flows into an additional warm family room that opens to a patio and private backyard, ideal for entertaining or quiet evenings. Two bedrooms and a brand new spa-like full bath complete this main level. Upstairs, enjoy the primary suite with a balcony porch overlooking the river and direct backyard access, and an additional bedroom and sleek modern bath. Additional amenities include: a private laundry room in the lower level, central & split units cooling and heating systems, and a one car garage plus driveway parking. Additional Street Parking (across the street & along the stone wall by 20 Terrace Dr). Conveniently located near major highways and the Mario Cuomo (Tappan Zee) Bridge, with easy access to the vibrant shops, dining, and riverfront parks of Nyack and Piermont. This unique and exceptional home blends luxury, comfort, and convenience. Tenant is responsible for all utilities, snow removal, and landscaping. Perhaps the best luxury rental option in Nyack!

Beautiful 3-bedroom apt in the heart of the Village of Warwick, NY. Lovely Victorian Farmhouse duplex offers character, charm, ample storage, and a stunning backyard on 2/3 of an acre. Just a few minutes from shops, eateries, the library, and parks. This location simply can't be beat. Features include 10' ceilings, commercial oven/stove, updated bathrooms including a stackable washer and dryer in unit, driveway parking, beautiful patio, and fire pit area. Walk-up attic and basement provide tons of storage. Tenant pays: utilities, private garbage, & snow removal. Landlord will maintain lawn care. Tenant to pay 1 month brokerage fee, 1 month security, and 1st month's rent at lease signing. Credit score of 725 or above. Dogs will be considered, no cats. Stainless steel kitchen bar table and stools can be included if the tenant is interested in using them or the landlord can remove. No access to any accessory buildings. Showings Available starting on Friday 7/18/25.

You also get to enjoy the lifestyle of living just moments from the picturesque downtown and waterfront areas of Hastings-on-Hudson featuring restaurants, boutique shops, parks, trails, and a community pool. Feel at home in the bright foyer as you enter this multi-family home. Sunlight streams into this apartment. The living room is open to the formal dining room, both featuring hardwood floors. Enjoy the updated eat-in-kitchen with new appliances, ample cabinet storage, and access to the private balcony overlooking the garden. The primary bedroom features 2 double closets and ensuite primary bathroom. 2 additional bedrooms with hardwood floors and ample closet space. A full hall bathroom completes this move-in ready apartment. Private laundry.

text: Welcome to this Elegant Victorian Home For Rent in Rockaway Park and all just steps from the bay or beach! Experience refined coastal living in this grand six-bedroom, four-bathroom Victorian home, perfectly situated just two blocks from the Atlantic shoreline and the famous Rockaway Beach boardwalk. Offering both short-term and long-term rental options, this residence is a rare opportunity to enjoy timeless elegance with modern convenience in New York's #1 and ONLY oceanfront community. Set on an expansive 6000SF lot with private parking for up to six vehicles, the home welcomes you with exquisite period details, soaring ceilings, and sun-drenched living spaces. A huge entrance foyer, both a formal living and dining room, kitchen and full bathroom on the first floor create an ideal setting for both intimate gatherings and large-scale entertaining. Upstairs, you'll find six spacious bedrooms, each designed for comfort and privacy, along with three more beautifully appointed bathrooms some featuring elegant finishes. Outdoor areas provide the perfect backdrop for morning coffee on the front porch, evening cocktails, or simply relaxing after a day at the beach. Located just minutes from the NYC Ferry, one block to the A train and buses, fine dining, boutique, big box shopping and more, this home offers the perfect balance of serene seaside retreat and convenient city access. Property Highlights: - 6 Bedrooms / 4 Bathrooms - 3000SF of living space on a 6000SF lot - Parking for 6 cars - private and secure garage - Historic Victorian charm with modern upgrades - Across the street from the bay and 2 blocks from Rockaway Beach - Flexible lease terms: short- or long-term - Exceptional location near transportation, shopping and restaurants. - Price includes heat - tenant pays cooking gas and electric. - Pets ok Great for long of short term rentals, the space is perfect for someone doing renovations in their own home. If that's you, give us a call to discuss rates. Have any questions about length of lease or pricing, don't hesitate to reach out. This is more than a rental-it's a lifestyle and we're hear to help. See you soon!
